UnitBatchRelayer::constructor
└── When called
    └── It sets the max relay fee BPS

UnitBatchRelayer::batchRelay
├── When calling a native asset pool
│   ├── It gets the asset from the pool
│   ├── It call withdraw() on the pool for each proof
│   ├── It transfers the assets to the recipient
│   ├── It transfers the fees to the fee recipient
│   └── It emits an event
├── When calling a non-native asset pool
│   ├── It gets the asset from the pool
│   ├── It call withdraw() on the pool for each proof
│   ├── It transfers the assets to the recipient
│   ├── It transfers the fees to the fee recipient
│   └── It emits an event
├── When proofs array is empty
│   └── It reverts with EmptyProofs
├── When relay fee BPS is greater than max relay fee BPS
│   └── It reverts with InvalidRelayFeeBPS
├── When contract balance has changed after the batch relay
│   └── It reverts with BalanceChanged
└── When batch size is different than the number of proofs
    └── It reverts with InvalidBatchSize

UnitBatchRelayer::_transfer
├── When recipient is zero
│   └── It reverts with ZeroAddress
├── When asset is native
│   ├── When transfer fails
│   │   └── It reverts with NativeAssetTransferFailed
│   └── When transfer succeeds
│       └── It transfers the amount to the recipient
└── When asset is not native
    └── It calls .transfer() on the asset

UnitBatchRelayer::_assetBalance
├── When asset is native
│   └── It returns the contract balance
└── When asset is not native
    └── It returns the asset balance of the contract

UnitBatchRelayer::_deductFee
└── When called
    └── It returns the correct amount